Photo by @johnstanmeyer / Cheap manual labor fuels India’s economy. Boatman Sarjeet Singh ferries people and supplies across the Beas. The river is filled with toxins from industrial plants along its shores, which have decimated fish populations. This is from my story "Water Everywhere, and Nowhere," in the August issue, now on newsstands worldwide.
