Photo by @johnstanmeyer / A man dresses after morning prayers and ablutions on a foggy morning along the Yamuna River in Prayagraj (Allahabad). The coils of electric cabling would later power a religious gathering along three of India’s great rivers at the Triveni Sangan, where the Yamuna, Saraswati, and the Ganges rivers converge. This is from my latest story in @natgeo magazine, "Water Everywhere, and Nowhere," in the August issue, now on newsstands worldwide.
